<DOCNO> XIE20000127.0003 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ECOWAS Calls to End Sierra Leone Attacks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, January 26 (Xinhua) -- The Economic Community of West
African states (ECOWAS) Wednesday called on former fighters in
Sierra Leone to halt attacks on civilians. The Community said
in a statement published in Freetown that the peace agreement
signed last July was being continually violated, reported the
British Broadcast Corporation (BBC) on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
It called on former combatants to dismantle illegal roadblocks
and to free child soldiers.
</P>
<P>
The statement came a day after a high-level meeting in Freetown
of the Joint Implementation Committee on the peace accord, which
is chaired by ECOWAS. Most former fighters have not disarmed
under the peace agreement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
