<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Annan Hails Successful Completion of Elections in Guinea-Bissau </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, January 27 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan Thursday welcomed the successful completion of
elections in Guinea-Bissau and commended its people for
demonstrating a firm commitment to democracy and peace and for
working together to overcome recent difficulties.
</P>
<P>
In a statement released here by his spokesman, Annan, who is
in Moscow on a three-day visit to Russia, extended his warm
congratulations to president-elect, Kumba Yala, and to the interim
President, Malam Bacai Sanha, for the "positive and statesmanlike
manner in which they conducted their electoral campaign."
</P>
<P>
Noting that Guinea-Bissau would need international cooperation
to consolidate its newly restored democracy and enhance prospects
for sustainable development, Annan reaffirmed continued U.N.
support and appealed to the international community to provide
urgently needed assistance to the new government.
</P>
<P>
The results of the January 16 presidential elections were
officially announced by Guinea-Bissau's National Electoral
Commission on January 21.
</P>
<P>
The elections were seen as a key step toward restoring
normalcy to the former Portuguese colony of 1.1 million people
after a devastating 11-month conflict. The civil war culminated in
President Joao Bernardo Vieira's ouster in May last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
