<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Swiss President Calls for Responsible Globalization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAVOS, SWITZERLAND, January 27 (Xinhua) -- President of the
Swiss confederation Adlof Ogi called on world leaders in politics
and business to proceed with globalization in a responsible manner.
</P>
<P>
Speaking here Thursday at the opening of the annual meeting of
the World Economic Forum (WEF), Ogi told the participants that "it
is up to you to ensure free-trade is compatible with the good of
the global community.".
</P>
<P>
He said that while capital movements could generate progress,
productivity and prosperity, they could also force whole economies
and nations into depression.
</P>
<P>
The Swiss president said that this power meant that industry
and commerce had growing social responsibilities, and that the
evolution of the world economy should therefore be determined by
society as a whole.
</P>
<P>
He reminded his audience of the protests at last year's trade
summit in Seattle and said these was "a clear sign of the mistrust
felt by many regarding globalization".
</P>
<P>
Ogi said the chief aim of the economy was not to generate
maximum profits for shareholders, but rather to help achieve
liberty and justice. He said politicians should therefore seek a
more global role, by fixing global rules for economic development.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
