<DOCNO> XIE20000127.0012 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zanzibar Defense Counsels Seek Dismissal of Treason Charge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
 DAR ES SALAAM, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Defense counsels in
Zanzibar treason case involving 18 opposition Civic United Front
(CUF) activists Thursday asked the High Court to dismiss the
charge because the Isles does not stand as a sovereign state and
therefore cannot be overthrown.
</P>
<P>
"The treason cannot be committed as Zanzibar is not a
sovereign state," the advocate Hamid Bwezeleni told the court
which was also attended by CUF Secretary General Seif Sharriff
Hamad and the party's Vice Chairman Shaaban Mloo.
</P>
<P>
 Zanzibar had seized to exist as an independent state since
April 1964, after it surrendered its sovereignty as a result of a
merger with the then Tanganyika, explained him.
</P>
<P>
Bwezeleni, the former Attorney General in Zanzibar, was
supported by another defense counsel Ussi Khamis, who said the
case is time barred due to the prosecution's delay to start
hearing of the trial for over two years.
</P>
<P>
Under the Zanzibar laws of criminal procedures, a person
suspected for the treason must be tried by the prosecution within
two years since the offence is committed, he said.
</P>
<P>
The defense counsels objected to an application raised by a
senior state attorney Othman Makungu who seeks for adjournment to
enable the new Attorney General Saleh Dahoma to study the case
file and get prepared for the trial.
</P>
<P>
Makungu said the case file had been handed over to the new
Attorney General on Wednesday following the removal of his
predecessor Ali Mohammed Omar.
</P>
<P>
In their submission, the counsels said it was not fair to
grant the adjournment on grounds that the case file was in the AG
chamber for a long time and the change of prosecutors is not an
excuse at all.
</P>
<P>
However, the Nigerian Judge chairing the court Garba Tumaka
adjourned the session until February 28 this year.
</P>
<P>
He said he expects the prosecution will at that time be in a
position to respond to the arguments raised by the defense
counsels and to begin hearing of the trial.
</P>
<P>
The 18 defendants were arrested on charges they conspired to
overthrow President Salmin Amour of the semi-autonomous Zanzibar
region in the Indian Ocean off mainland Tanzania. Four of the
suspects are members of Zanzibar's 50-seat Parliament.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
