<DOCNO> XIE20000127.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egyptian Parliament Passes New Family Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Egypt's People's Assembly (lower
house) endorsed on Wednesday night an amendment introduced by the
government to a new family draft bill, making divorce easier for
women.
</P>
<P>
The personal status draft law allows the wife to get divorced in
return for waiving all her financial entitlements from the
marriage, including dowry and other gifts from the husband, as well
as alimony.
</P>
<P>
Under the previous law, an Egyptian man can end his marriage
simply by filing a paper with the marriage registrar, while a woman
seeking divorce faced years of legal procedures.
</P>
<P>
The parliament rejected an article that would allow the wife to
travel without the consent of her husband, saying that Islamic
religious junctures give the husband the right to decide whether
his wife will travel or not.
</P>
<P>
The new law allows the couples involved in orfi (unofficial)
marriages to go to court for divorce. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000127.0015 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran to Launch Military Exercises to Mark Revolution Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Iranian army will launch a one-
day military exercises on Saturday on the eve of the "10-day Dawn"
to celebrate the 21st anniversary of the 1979 Islamic revolution,
an army commander announced on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The commander Brigadier General Reza Moradi said that the
exercises named "Fajr (Dawn) 21" will be held in Ahvaz and Dezful
of the southwestern province of Khuzestan, the Islamic Republic
News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The "10-day Dawn" celebration starts on February 1 to mark the
return of late Iranian supreme leader Ayatollah Musavi Khomeini
from France in 1979 and will culminate in a massive rally on
February 11, the Day of Victory of the Islamic Revolution.
</P>
<P>
Moradi said the army's air force, airborne units of the ground
force and 10,000 troops of the ground force as well as dozens of
jet fighters and bombers will take part in the three-stage military
games.
</P>
<P>
The army's units will exercise rapid deployment within the least
possible time, joint operation of the air force, the ground force
and the airborne troops with employment of the latest techniques in
an area of 2,000 square kilometers, he said.
</P>
<P>
The commander said the objective of the exercises is to examine
operational coordination and boost preparedness of the army units
in southern Iran. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
