<DOCNO> XIE20000127.0018 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkey to Woo Foreign Investment at Davos </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Prime Minister Bulent
Ecevit will make efforts to encourage foreign investment in Turkey
during his presence at the upcoming annual World Economic Forum
(WEF) at Davos, Switzerland, the Anatolia News Agency reported on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Ecevit arrived at the Swiss city Thursday afternoon bearing a
full load of project proposals. He will display 58 public sector
projects to potential foreign investors.
</P>
<P>
He is due to deliver to international business circles a 22-page
report which will provide an overview of the Turkish economy and
pointing out investment opportunities in Turkey's public sector.
</P>
<P>
"Turkey will continue to promote a healthier economy by curbing
inflation, continuing with privatization, removing all impediments
for a bilateral and competitive market economy and creating a more
positive environment for foreign investment," said the report,
which was made available for the press in advance.
</P>
<P>
The report declared that Turkey plans to invest 30 billion U.S.
dollars over the next decade in the energy sector. "This will
provide an excellent opportunity for foreign investors who seek
economically sound projects in a stable environment," the report
said.
</P>
<P>
The report highlighted Turkey's massive privatization programs
and infrastructure projects of the private sector. The so-called
Build-Operate-Transfer (BOT) model will be promoted in transport
and urban infrastructure investments, it noted.
</P>
<P>
Ecevit, accompanied by Foreign Minister Ismail Cem, has a full
diary during his three-day stay in Davos.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the WEF sessions, Ecevit is scheduled to hold a
meeting with the Business Interaction Group, comprising investors
interested in Turkey. He is also expected to meet British Prime
Minister Tony Blair and Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak among
others.
</P>
<P>
The WEF annual summit is an opportunity for international
political and business leaders to discuss economic, financial and
technological trends and other issues of global importance.
</P>
<P>
Technical revolution and globalization are expected to be high
on the agenda of this year's forum, which will be held on January
27-February 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
