<HEADLINE> Belgium Maintains Move Against Pinochet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Belgium and the human rights
groups still want to prevent Pinochet's release, local media said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Hith Court in London Wednesday examined a request from
Belgium and six human rights groups to force Britain to allow
further medical checks on Chile's former leader, General Pinochet.
</P>
<P>
Belgium and the human rights groups are protesting against
secrecy surrounding the medical report from British doctors.
British Home Secretary Jack Straw is basing his possible decision
to release Pinochet on this report, which claims that Pinochet is
not fit to stand trial. The High Court ruling is still awaited.
</P>
<P>
The Belgian government has decided, however, not to take a case
to the court of human rights in The Hague if this procedure fails.
Belgian Foreign Minister Louis Michel has said he does not want a
political conflict with Britain, local media reported. 
</P>
