<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 27 (Xinhua) -- France called on Iraq on Thursday
to cooperate with the United Nations new inspector of disarmament
Hans Blix, who will lead a new arms control commission in Iraq.
</P>
<P>
French Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Anne Gazeau-Secret said
that the U.N. Resolution 1284, which resumes cooperation between
Iraq and U.N. and could lead to a suspension of sanctions, ``is an
opportunity to seize'' for Iraq.
</P>
