<HEADLINE> Greek Parliamentarians Call for Elian's Return to Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, January 27 (Xinhua) -- About 40 Greek parliamentarians
Thursday called on the U.N. Secretary General Kofi Annan to help
end the ongoing tug of war between the United State and Cuba over
the six-year-old Elian Gonzalez to ensure that the child is
returned to his father.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to Annan, the Greek parliamentarians said that the
issue should be tackled within the context of humanitarian laws,
adding that their decision was reached on the basis of the
consideration of the child's "obvious need to return to his
natural family environment which, in the wake of the death of his
mother, will ensure the requisite emotional support."
</P>
<P>
The parliamentarians are members of the Greek Parliament's
Standing Committee on Defense and Foreign Affairs, and
representing the ruling Panhellenic Socialist Movement (PASOK),
the main opposition New Democracy (ND), the Communist Party of
Greece (KKE), the Left Coalition and the Democratic Social
Movement.
</P>
<P>
Elian was picked up at sea off Florida last November, but his
mother drowned when a boat full of illegal Cuban immigrants
capsized.
</P>
