<HEADLINE> Market Shooting Kills 4 in Somali Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, January 27 (Xinhua) -- At least four people were
killed and more than eight others were wounded when rival
militiamen exchanged heavy gunfire in the heart of Mogadishu's
largest Bakara market Wednesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
As the shooting subsided, two dead bodies were seen in the
market while the wounded were rushed to a nearby treatment center.
</P>
<P>
Two more people also died of the wounds in the treatment center
later in the evening.
</P>
<P>
A relative of one of the deceased said the tragedy broke out
after a small business owner was robbed of his goods by gunmen.
</P>
<P>
The relative who remained anonymous added that the robbed man
together with other several gunmen returned to the scene looking
for the bandits.
</P>
<P>
However, the shooting began as the looters recognized the men
who were looking for them.
</P>
<P>
The security situation around the main market of Bakara has
been so terrible ever since the more than 100-strong force of
security guards organized by the major businessmen were disbanded
last June.
</P>
<P>
Mogadishu remains volatile as the movement of weapons continues
to be out of control since there is no central authority 10 years
after the collapse of the late regime. 
</P>
