<HEADLINE> China Pockets Third Gold at World Cup Diving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Li Na and Sang Xue claimed the
women's 10 meters synchronized platform title Thursday night to
bring China's haul to three golds on the third day of the FINA
Diving World Cup at the Sydney Olympic pool.
</P>
<P>
Russian superstar Dmitriy Sautin showed his outstanding
abilities in diving again by snatching the gold in the 3-meter
springboard. Xiao Hailiang of China had to settle for the second
place.
</P>
<P>
Sautin won the 10-meter platform at the 1996 Atlanta Olympics
and bronze at the 1992 Barcelona Games and took out the 3-meter
and 10-meter finals at the 1998 world championships.
</P>
<P>
When asked about how he would act in September, Sautin said the
Olympics is very special and there would be a lot of pressure on
everybody. "It is very difficult to predict what would happen." He
added.
</P>
<P>
Li Na won the women's 10 meters platform title and Chinese pair
Xiong Ni and Xiao Hailiang triumphed in the men's 3-meter
synchronized diving on Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
