<HEADLINE> Beijing Aims to Fully Utilize Overseas Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Beijing is making efforts to
cultivate a diversified investment environment this year with the
aim of effectively utilizing overseas funds.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Mao, deputy mayor, said at an Economic and Trade
Conference today that while continuing to promote overseas funds
in the public sector, Beijing will exert more efforts to encourage
the private sector to attract more overseas investments.
</P>
<P>
Central government organizations in Beijing and local
enterprises in other provinces are also welcomed to establish
joint ventures in Beijing, he said.
</P>
<P>
Official sources said that Beijing actually used overseas
investment worth 2.94 billion U.S. dollars last year, an increase
of 2.3 percent from 1998.
</P>
<P>
By introducing new ways of using overseas funds such as BOT (
build, operate, transfer), stock listing on overseas bourses and
issuing bonds, the capital hopes to sign more agreements on
attracting overseas investment this year.
</P>
<P>
Beijing will also try to create favorable conditions for
overseas capital into auction markets in Chinese enterprises.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
