<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Contract for HK's West Rail Tunnel Ventilation System Awarded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 27 (Xinhua) -- The Kowloon-Canton Railway
Corporation today announced the award of the contract for West
Rail's Tunnel Ventilation System at a value of 104.94 million HK
dollars (13.5 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
With the award of the contract, a total of 16 civil
construction contracts and 13 railway operation systems contracts
have so far been awarded at a total value of about 26 billion HK
dollars (3.3 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The ventilation system will cover about 14 kilometers of the 30.
5-kilometer railway and three enclosed stations, namely Nam Cheong
Station, Mei Foo Station and Tsuen Wan West Station.
</P>
<P>
The construction of West Rail Phase I is packaged into 17 civil
construction contracts and 20 railway operation systems contracts.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the West Rail (Phase I), which connects West
Kowloon and Tuen Mun via Yuen Long, started in October 1998 and is
due to be completed by the end of 2003.  
</P>
</TEXT>
