<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Seminar Urges Taiwan's Reunification with Motherland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Participants in a seminar held
here this afternoon said that the Taiwan question cannot drag on
with indefinite duration and the tide of Taiwan's reunification
with the motherland is irresistible.
</P>
<P>
The seminar was held to mark the fifth anniversary of an eight-
point proposal made by Chinese President Jiang Zemin on the
resolution of the Taiwan question. More than 80 people from
various social sectors in Macao took part in the seminar.
</P>
<P>
About a dozen participants delivered speeches. They noted that
Jiang's eight-point proposal is the actual practice and
development of Deng Xiaoping's "peaceful reunification, one
country, two systems" concept, and is the guiding principle for
reasonably resolving the Taiwan question at the current situation.
</P>
<P>
The successful resolution of the Hong Kong and Macao issues
makes the Taiwan question more outstanding, the speakers said,
adding that the principles of "one country, two systems" and a
high degree of autonomy in Hong Kong and Macao will surely play an
exemplary role for Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Following its return to the motherland, Macao will maintain its
unique role as a bridge between the two sides of the Taiwan
Straits, and will contribute more to promoting the development of
cross-Straits relations and the resolution of the Taiwan question,
the participants said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
