<HEADLINE> Thai Automobile Output Surges in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's automobile
production in 1999 more than doubled from 1998 while the vehicle
exports also rose sharply, the Bangkok Post said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Citing figures from the Federation of Thai Industries, the
newspaper said the automobile production in Thailand rose by 106.9
percent to 327,233 units, of which 72,716 were cars and 240,369
were one-ton pickup trucks.
</P>
<P>
Production of all types of trucks including one-ton pickups
reached 248,614 units, while other types of vehicles included 5,
822 station wagons and 81 ten-ton coaches.
</P>
<P>
Motorcycle production totaled 846,426 units, a rise of 43.9
percent.
</P>
<P>
Vehicle exports rose by 85.2 percent to 125,702 units, with the
value rising 78.4 percent to 50.19 billion baht (1.34 billion U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
However, motorcycle exports fell by 86.8 percent to 32,288
units worth 1.07 billion baht (28.6 million dollars), down 87.3
percent.
</P>
<P>
Total automotive product exports, including vehicles,
motorcycles,engines and parts, were worth 68.59 billion baht (1.83
billion dollars), a 55.3 percent increase from 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
