<DOCNO> XIE20000127.0100 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bomb Explosion Kills 10 in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 27 (Xinhua) -- At least 10 people were killed
and 39 others wounded on Thursday when a powerful bomb exploded in
a letter box in the northern Sri Lankan town of Vavuniya, the
Defense Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
"A bomb which had been inside the outgoing foreign letter box
exploded at the Vavuniya post office today around 11:20 a.m. (0520
GMT)," said a ministry statement.
</P>
<P>
The explosion killed 10 persons and wounded 12 soldiers, seven
police personnel and 20 civilians, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
Officials said the soldiers were at the post office to send
money to their families in the south of Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
Rescue operations have been conducted to rush the wounded to
the nearby hospitals.
</P>
<P>
The bombing came despite tight security throughout the country
amid fears of more bomb attacks by the separatist Liberation
Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) rebels who are fighting for an
independent homeland for minority Tamils in Sri Lanka's north and
east since 1983.
</P>
<P>
The bomb attacks have been the trademark of the LTTE rebels who
are blamed for a series of suicide bomb attacks in recent weeks
against President Chandrika Kumaratunga and other senior officials.
</P>
<P>
The ministry statement said government troops killed nine LTTE
rebels in four separate clashes in the northernmost Jaffna
peninsula, the stronghold of the rebels until 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
