<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Expects to Harvest Record Wheat Output </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan may harvest a record
21 million metric tons of wheat in the year 2000 following a 15-
percent increase in the wheat growing areas,a senior official said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He said that if the country had two more spells of rain in
February and March, no doubt Pakistan would harvest a record 21
million tons against the target of 20 million tons.
</P>
<P>
The official said that recent spells of rain had very positive
effect on this crop in the South Asian country. The wheat
harvesting season is to start on March 15 in the southern province
of Sindh. 
</P>
</TEXT>
