<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 27 (Xinhua) -- The Kuala Lumpur Stock
Exchange closed mixed Thursday.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index lost 1.36
points to 939.59, the all-share Emas Index added 0.21 of a point
to 239.14, the Industrial Index dipped 3.35 points to 1,549.8 and
the Second Board Index gained 2.47 points to 212.13.
</P>
<P>
Gainers led losers by 399 to 329 while 118 counters were
unchanged, 101 counters untraded and eight others suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover stood at 596.87 million shares valued at 1.
545 billion ringgit (406.578 million U.S. dollars) against 1.059
billion shares valued at 2.508 billion ringgit (660 million
dollars) on Wednesday. 
</P>
