<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rats Infest 160 Hectares of Farmlands in Central  Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Some 160 hectares of ricelands
in central part of the Philippines have been infested by rat,
Philippine News Agency said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted Abednego Gerona, a local agriculture official,
as saying that the area suffer from the rat infestation involves
nine villages in Siaton of Negros Oriental province in Visayas.
</P>
<P>
Gerona said the rat infestation has affected some 663 farmers
in these villages.
</P>
<P>
He said the situation is not so "larming" considering that only
35-36 percent has been reportedly affected of the total rice
farmlands of Siaton.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, farmers of these villages, in which farming
is the only means of livelihood, have greatly affected their rice
production.
</P>
<P>
Gerona hopes the financial counterpart from local government
will help assist the farmers in their purchase of "rodenticides",
a product which poisons rat. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
