<DOCNO> XIE20000127.0121 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia to Require Political Parties to Hold Elections Regularly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, January 27 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government will
introduce a new law requiring political parties to hold elections
regularly to inculcate the culture of democracy in the country,
the Zambia Daily Mail newspaper reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Zambian Home Affairs Minister Peter Machungwa told parliament
Wednesday that his ministry will ensure that political parties
regularize elections and live by their constitutional provisions.
</P>
<P>
There are currently about forty political parties in the
southern African country, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Most political parties still have interim committees from the
time they were registered and are unwilling to undergo elections,
the minister noted.
</P>
<P>
The new law will compel these political parties to specify
within their provisional requirements to elect, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
