<DOCNO> XIE20000127.0122 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Abortion Kills 4,300 Kenyan Women Per Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Some 4,300 Kenyan women of
reproductive age die of pregnancy-related complications every
year, the Nurses Association of Kenya has said.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey in six districts of the east African country
showed that 35 percent of the gynecological ward admissions were
due to incomplete abortions, said Heme Ndung'u, secretary of the
nurses association.
</P>
<P>
However, the data underestimated the extent of the problem
since they presented only those women admitted to hospitals for
treatment, the Kenya Times newspaper Thursday quoted the nurse
boss as saying.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Kenya's senior health officials proposed to legalize
abortion but met with stiff resistance from religious community
and some conservatives.
</P>
<P>
Due to the illegal status of abortion, many Kenyan women turn
to quacks or witch doctors, which have caused many unnecessary
tragedies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
