<HEADLINE> Sudan Releases 54 Abducted Ugandan Kids </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 27 (Xinhua) -- The Sudanese government has
handed over to the United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF) 54
Ugandan children abducted by rebels of the Lord's Resistance Army
(LRA) fighting Kampala authorities.
</P>
<P>
These children are aged between six and 18 years, a UNICEF
official was quoted as saying by Thursday's New Vision newspaper.
</P>
<P>
The abducted children were released under a peace accord signed
by Uganda and Sudan in the Kenyan capital Nairobi on December 8
last year.
</P>
<P>
Uganda released the last batch of Sudanese prisoners of war
earlier this month.
</P>
<P>
The LRA rebels have been fighting against the Ugandan
government since 1986 and the UNICEF estimates that more than
10,000 Ugandans have been kidnapped in the past five years.
</P>
