<HEADLINE> Angolan Refugees Sell Guns in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Angolan refugees at Mayukwayukwa
camp in Zambia's Western Province are selling guns to earn a
living, a Zambia daily Mail newspaper reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Villagers in the area buying the guns from the refugees and
reselling them to people who are traveling there, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Some refugees revealed that they hide arsenal on their way to
the camps in Zambia and retrieve the arms later after settling
down in camps.
</P>
<P>
The villagers around the refugee settlement alleged that some
refugees were crossing into the country with guns which they were
later selling to them for killing people.
</P>
<P>
They appealed to the Zambian government to help in tracking
down the criminals in the refugee camps.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Home Affairs Peter Machungwa said refugees breaking
the law would be treated like any other offender.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the United Nations High Commission for Refugees
(UNHCR) said that it would strive to ease and improve the
deplorable conditions refugees were living in. 
</P>
