<HEADLINE> U.S. Companies Agree to Distribute Management Solution With Linux </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, January 26 (Xinhua) -- Computer Associates
International Inc. (CA and Red Hat Inc. agreed Wednesday to work
together in distributing CA's management solution with Linux
operating system.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the two companies will enable their
clients to achieve integrated support of CA's extensive mission-
critical IT application running on Red Hat's Linux Enterprise
Editions series, one of the fastest-growing operating systems.
</P>
<P>
Linux is emerging as a leading technology platform for mission-
critical applications and Web-based commerce, which would
challenge Microsoft's Windows operating system.
</P>
<P>
"As the world's premier supplier of IT management solutions for
eBusiness, CA recognizes the crucial role that the Linux operating
platform has assumed within today's highly competitive business
landscape and technology infrastructures," said CA president and
chief operating officer, Sanjay Kumar.
</P>
<P>
"CA is pleased that Red Hat chose to work with CA to offer
Linux clients the first integrated enterprise management solution
that will be used by clients throughout the world."
</P>
<P>
A recent survey revealed that 48 percent of enterprise
customers view Linux as an important component to their enterprise
IT strategy for 2000, said CA and Red Hat in a news release.
</P>
<P>
"The combination of Red Hat Linux and a full implementation of
CA's technology bring new levels of data protection to the Linux
operating system," said Pascal Wattiaux, vice president of
technology at Quokka Sports.
</P>
<P>
"CA and Red Hat are working together to clearly demonstrate
that the Linux platform can provide the basis of an industrial-
strength eBusiness solution." 
</P>
</TEXT>
