<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Prime Minister Worried About Austria's Extreme Right </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 27 (Xinhua) -- French Prime Minister Lionel
Jospin said on Thursday that although France respects Austria, a
possible coming to power of the country's extreme-right would be a
"disturbing event."
</P>
<P>
In a statement made to Swedish television in Stockholm, where
he was making a visit, Jospin also said that France would not
interfere into the political life of Austria, according to Agence
France-Presse.
</P>
<P>
"There is no danger of Nazism, or danger for the Jewish
community in Austria or any other European and democratic
countries at the same time, it is a disturbing event," Jospin was
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister said that all those whose ideas about Hitler
and racism were not clear "are a potential threat."
</P>
<P>
The Austrian extreme-right PFOe led by Joerg Haider is
negotiating with other parties on the formation of a coalition,
after it became the second largest party in the October election.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
