<HEADLINE> Gebrselassie Pulls out of Indoor Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 26 (Xinhua) -- Double world indoor champion
Haile Gebrselassie of Ethiopia has pulled out of all indoor track
competitions this season because an Achilles tendor affected his
training since last year.
</P>
<P>
"He's training but after his injury he's not in top shape, so
we cancelled his indoor competitions," Gebrselassie's Dutch
manager Jos Hermens said in Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
Four times world 10,000 meters champion outdoors, Gebrselassie
expects to defend his Olympic 10,000 meters title in Sydney,
Hermens said.
</P>
<P>
Gebrselassie's first international competition of the year is
likely to be on May 28 in the Dutch town of Hengelo where he
usually starts his outdoor season. 
</P>
