<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Davenport Reaches Final of Australian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Lindsay Davenport outpowered
Jennifer Capriati in straight sets to reach the final of the
Australian Open in Melbourne on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Despite her strained left thigh, Davenport breezed across
Capriati 6-2, 7-6 (7-4) in the one-hour-22-minute competition, a
conflict of baseline attacks.
</P>
<P>
Taking the first set in 22 minutes, Davenport, the second seed
in the tournament, dropped only five points on serve and twice
breaking Capriati's service.
</P>
<P>
However, Capriati showed her old competitiveness when she
fought back from 2-4 in the second set, winning eight straight
points to tie the set at 4-4 and broke for the third time in the
set to force the tiebreaker.
</P>
<P>
At 4-4 in the tiebreaker, Capriati yielded with a backhand into
the net, then barely missed a return wide to fall behind 6-4.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
