<HEADLINE> Sking Races cancelled for Too Little Snow in Salt Lake City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Too little snow leads to
cancel the womens' World Cup skiing races set to be held in Salt
Lake City between February 6 and 12 on Thursday, according to the
International Ski Federation (FIS).
</P>
<P>
FIS said that temperatures were too high to make enough
artificial snow to cover the course and they would try and find
another venue in Europe that could host the programme of one
downhill, a Super-G, a slalom and the only womens' combined race
of the season.  
</P>
