<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Korea Overwhelm Chinese Taipei in Asian Handball Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 27 (Xinhua) -- South Korean women trounced
Chinese Taipei 34-8 to score their third straight victory at the
Asian handball championships in Yamaga, Japan on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Atlanta Olympic silver medallists struggled to cope with
the slow rhythm of Chinese Taipei in the first 10 minutes, scoring
only one goal through Jang Sun-Young.
</P>
<P>
After Kim Jin-Soon came in to replace Kim Hyang-Ki and scored
in the 12th minute, the South Koreans netted another seven goals
until Kung Ju-wen made one back for Chinese Taipei in the 20th
minute to make it 8-1.
</P>
<P>
South Korea won the lopsided game by 26 points finally with Kim
Jin-Soon scoring six goals and Jang finishing with a tally of
eight.
</P>
<P>
South Korea stood with three wins against no defeat in the five-
squad round robin and got closer to their seventh straight Asian
championship and a berth in the Sydney Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
In the other game, Japanese women's team narrowly edged DPR.
Korea 26-25 with Masako Okidoi scoring a winner 28 seconds from
the end of the game.
</P>
<P>
In the men's competition in Kumamoto, China came from behind to
beat Bangkok bronze medallists Japan 24-20. Japan led at the half-
time 11-9.
</P>
<P>
On the team standings, the Chinese tied with Asian Games
champions South Korea with two wins each and they will face each
other on Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
