<DOCNO> XIE20000127.0155 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Agassi Wins Epic Semi at Australian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 27 (Xinhua) -- World No.1 Andre Agassi
weathered a Pete Sampras storm to force his way into the
Australian Open men's singles final at the Melbourne Park in
Melbourne Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
Agassi came back from two sets to one down to win 6-4, 3-6, 6-7
(0-7), 7-6 (7-5), 6-1 in a match that lived up to almost every
expectation.
</P>
<P>
The 1995 Australian champion and the championships' top seed
appeared destined for an early departure as the ice-cold Sampras
repeatedly blasted his way out of trouble.
</P>
<P>
But with victory within his grasp, Sampras faltered, losing the
fourth set tiebreak and offering unusually weak resistance in the
fifth.
</P>
<P>
In a match which started tentatively, Sampras' play failed to
reach its highest level.
</P>
<P>
For most of the match he was held in check by Agassi, the
difference being his ability to produce a booming serve when it
was needed most.
</P>
<P>
Agassi drew first blood, breaking serve in the fifth game of
the first set and never allowing his opponent a chance to do the
same.
</P>
<P>
For Sampras, the defeat destroyed his 8-0 record in five-
setters at the Australian Open, while for Agassi it narrowed the
gap between the two, their record now standing at 17-12 in favor
of Sampras. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000127.0156 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong, China, to Host Pakistan for Davis Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong, China, will host
the first round match in the 2000 Asia/Oceania Zone Group II for
the Davis Cup tennis tournament in Hong Kong from January 28 to 30,
Hong Kong Tennis Association announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Seeded Pakistan, which was beaten by China last year in the
Asia/Oceania Zone Group I, will field their best line-up to face
the host Hong Kong, China.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time the two teams will have clashed in the
cup history. Hong Kong defeated Pakistan 3-2 in 1992.
</P>
<P>
"The key point of the match is the doubles, " said Hong Kong's
trainer Xia Jiaping, a former Chinese player who won the men's
single title in World University Games in 1993.
</P>
<P>
"I am betting on Aisam-ul-Haq Qurashi in the match," said
Pakistan captain Khavaja Saeed Hai.
</P>
<P>
Nineteen-year-old Qurashi, now ranked 301st in the world, will
play both singles and doubles.
</P>
<P>
He will face Wayne Wong in the second singles on January 28 and
will team up with Asim Shafik to play doubles on January 29
against Andy Brothers/Andrew Town. He is to take on Melvin Tong in
the third singles on January 30.
</P>
<P>
Melvin is going to meet Asim Shafik in the first singles and
fight against Shafik in the fourth singles on January 30.
</P>
<P>
Davis Cup tennis, inaugurated in 1900, has been the top-level
annual tournament for the men's team tennis in the world.
</P>
<P>
The Asia Group II will be played for three rounds this year,
with the winner sailing into the Group I next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
