<HEADLINE> Information-Products Manufacturing Booms In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai has seen the rapid
development of its information-product manufacturing sector, which
reported a year-on-year 23.8 percent growth of output value last
year.
</P>
<P>
The industry reaped 4.341 billion yuan in profits in 1999, a 34.
29 percent rise over 1998, and paid 1.598 billion yuan in taxes,
up 13.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The sector's total assets amounted to 83.38 billion yuan in
1999, 11.8 billion yuan more than in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Output value of chemically made goods used for information
products registered the largest growth rate-- 55.8 percent last
year, while that for TV and broadcasting equipment went up by 32
percent, computers by 29.97 percent, and electronic components by
29.3 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
