<HEADLINE> Guangdong Passes New Rules on Emigration to HK and Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong Province in south
China, which borders Hong Kong and Macao, today announced new
rules for approving people to emigrate to the two special
administration regions.
</P>
<P>
According to a circular on the matter, emigration applicants
above age 60 will be listed in a special category which will be
given priority.
</P>
<P>
