<HEADLINE> Beijingers Satisfied with Public Security Conditions: Poll </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 27 (Xinhua) - A poll by the municipal
Statistics Bureau released today suggested that Beijing residents
were satisfied with the state of public security in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Among 4,100 households surveyed, 64 percent said they are
satisfied or comparatively satisfied with the public security
conditions around Beijing for the year, which is up 24 percent
over results from a survey taken in the first half of last year.
</P>
<P>
Beijing has taken three polls on public security since 1998.
The recent survey randomly selected 3,000 urban households and 1,
100 rural ones.
</P>
<P>
Sources with the public security department reported that the
number of criminal cases dropped 8.7 percent on an annual basis
last year. 
