<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East Timor Independence Leader Ends China Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Jose Alexandre Xanana Gusmao,
leader of the independence movements of East Timor and chairman of
CNRT, left here this afternoon after concluding his four-day visit
to China.
</P>
<P>
During Xanana's stay in the Chinese capital, Vice-President Hu
Jintao and Vice-Premier Qian Qichen met with him on separate
occasions. Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan also held talks
with the East Timorese independence leader.
</P>
<P>
China has participated in the United Nations Transitional
Administration in East Timor by sending civilian policemen and
officials.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, China has also announced a 50 million RMB yuan aid
package for East Timor's reconstruction during Xanana's visit to
China.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua before his departure from Beijing,
Xanana said that East Timor will establish diplomatic relations
with China as soon as it becomes independent.
</P>
<P>
He said he hopes China will contribute more to East Timor's
reconstruction
</P>
<P>
During Xanana's meetings with Chinese leaders in Beijing, the
two sides expressed the willingness to establish and develop
normal relations in the future. 
</P>
