<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Indian Ambassador K.V. Rajan
said India will not interfere with Nepal's security arrangements
or deploy any security forces in Nepal's international airport,
the Rising Nepal reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
At a reception to mark the 50th anniversary of India's Republic
Day on Wednesday, K.V. Rajan dismissed speculations that there was
some kind of interest on India's part to involve itself in Nepal's
security arrangements in the aftermath of hijacking.
</P>
