<HEADLINE> Foreign Trade Rising In Anhui Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, January 27 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province
reported a year-on-year 17.4 percent rise in foreign trade last
year with the total trade volume reaching 2.65 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
This includes 1.68 billion US dollars of exports and 970
million US dollars of imports.
</P>
<P>
As a result of the better Asian financial environment, Anhui's
exports to Japan, Asean, the ROK, and Taiwan amounted to 480
million US dollars in 1999, a 24.7 percent rise over 1998.
</P>
<P>
Anhui improved its export mix last year, as clothing rose by 7
percent, textile volume grow by 10 percent, and farm products
soared 39 percent.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the province's exports of electro-mechanical
products were valued at 270 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Of the total foreign trade in 1999, 1.76 billion US dollars
were brought in by local state-owned enterprises, up 9.3 percent
over the 1998 level, and 830 million US dollars by local overseas-
funded companies, an increase of 33.6 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
