<HEADLINE> Children and Students Urged to Drink High Quality Milk </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 27 (Xinhua) -- In a bid to improve the health
of students, Shanghai plans to have one million babies and primary
and secondary students, or half of the city's total, drink high
quality milk in the next three years.
</P>
<P>
Milk suppliers will enjoy preferential taxation treatment,
said an official in charge of Shanghai's milk industry.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, only 25 percent of the city's 2
million babies and primary and secondary students now drink milk
every day.
</P>
<P>
A sample survey conducted by the market supervision department
revealed that only 60 percent of the milk available in the city is
up to required standards.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai is one of the five cities selected by state
departments to take part in this experimental milk project.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Liaoning and Jiangsu provinces launched a campaign
urging primary and secondary school student to drink 250
milliliters of soybean milk or cow's milk a day.
</P>
<P>
The campaign is designed to wipe out anemia and rickets among
students and improve their health.  
</P>
</TEXT>
