<HEADLINE> Imports &AMP; Exports Reported Up In Shandong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, January 27 (Xinhua) -- The import and export trade of
east China's Shandong Province reached 18.27 billion US dollars
last year, a 10 percent rise over the 1998 figure.
</P>
<P>
The total includes 11.58 billion US dollars of exports, up 11.8
percent on a yearly basis and 5.7 percent higher than the national
average, and 6.69 billion US dollars of imports, up 6.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Among the year's exports, general trade reached 5.42 billion US
dollars, up 18 percent from 1998 level, and the remaining 6.13
billion US dollars were from the export of goods manufactured with
imported raw materials.
</P>
<P>
Shandong's exports to Asia grew by 15.5 percent year-on-year to
6.8 billion US dollars in 1999, the volume to the European Union
rose 7.2 percent to 1.55 billion US dollars, while exports to the
U.S. rose by 10.4 percent to 2.24 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Textiles and garments accounted for more than one-fourth of all
local exports, or 3 billion US dollars, the largest category of
local exports.
</P>
<P>
Shandong exported 2.7 billion US dollars worth of agricultural
and farm sideline products in 1999, up 17.4 percent on a yearly
basis, and 2.05 billion US dollars of electro-mechanical products,
up 7.1 percent over 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
