<HEADLINE> Myanmar Needs to Have Modern Army: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, January 27 (Xinhua) -- A high-ranking Myanmar military
official Wednesday stressed the need to have a modern, strong and
qualified army to safeguard a peaceful, stable, modern and
developed nation.
</P>
<P>
At a prize presentation ceremony here honoring winners of
military band competitions, Lieutenant-General Tin Oo, Chief of
Bureau of Special Operations and Chief of Staff of the Myanmar
Army, said the nation is modernizing the army and uplifting its
qualification for the nation to be free from aggressions and to
win esteem of the neighbors and to defend itself.
</P>
<P>
He recalled that Myanmar fell under subjugation as the country
had no permanent army in the past, emphasizing the importance of
building up military might by developing countries for regional
security as big countries are applying domination practices.
</P>
<P>
The general urged the armymen even better to respect and
observe the union spirit, warning that the national solidarity
will break up in the absence of union spirit and the nation will
lose independence and sovereignty again, making it impossible to
build a modern and developed nation. 
