<HEADLINE> Tourist Route to Nujiang Grand Gorge to Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Yunnan Province will open a
tourist route to the Nujiang Grand Gorge during the Kunming
International Tourism Festival, which begins on April 10.
</P>
<P>
The 800-km-long gorge in the Lisu Autonomous Prefecture of
Nujiang is the point of convergence for the Jinsha, Lancang (the
upper Mekong), and Nujiang rivers. It is a beautiful scenic spot,
the home to 12 ethnic groups, and is listed as one of the three
major biodiversity centers in China.
</P>
<P>
Five tourist zones have been opened at the grand gorge.
</P>
<P>
The gorge is a four hour flight from the provincial capital of
Kunming. The prefecture has 21 hotels which play host to more than
900,000 visitors annually. 
</P>
