<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, January 26 (Xinhua) -- The Colombian
government is negotiating an accord with the United States to
exchange information about the money deposits and investments made
by Colombian citizens in the U.S., an official said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The accord aims to oblige Colombians to pay taxes over the
money earned here and sent to the United States, said Director of
the National Taxation Department Guillermo Fino.
</P>
<P>
He noted that "the Colombian Legislation does not prohibit
having funds in foreign countries, as long as they are registered
in the Republic Bank to collect due taxes."
</P>
<P>
"The possible accord will allow the following up of capital
used to buy products that are brought to Colombia as smuggled
goods," he added. 
