<HEADLINE> Peru Registers Over 110 Earthquakes in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, January 26 (Xinhua) -- A total of 114 earthquakes were
felt and registered in Peru last year, mainly occurring during
April and August, said the Peruvian Geophysics Authority on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
It said 47 of them happened in the Pacific Ocean west of the
country, and 67 took place in the country's territory. Lima, the
capital city, was shaken by a considerable number of earthquakes,
and 14 tremors were felt in the Arequipa District.
</P>
<P>
On May 5, an earthquake measuring 5 magnitude on the Richter
scale hit Lima, the highest magnitude tremor affecting the city in
1999.
</P>
<P>
One of the strongest earthquakes last year happened in the
mountainous region of Chuschi, district of Ayacucho, with a
magnitude of six.
</P>
<P>
Peru is a seismic country, where authorities routinely keep the
population informed and take precautionary measures. 
</P>
