<DOCNO> XIE20000127.0259 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Tourist Spots to be Opened in Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, January 27 (Xinhua) -- The Tibet Autonomous Region is to
earmark 1.6 billion yuan to build nine key tourist resorts this
year.
</P>
<P>
At the top of the construction agenda are two state parks to be
built in the Yarlung Zangbo Grand Canyon. A new tourist route
passing through beautiful grassland and forest will be opened. The
three to four-day trip can be completed either on foot or on
horseback.
</P>
<P>
Other sightseeing spots to be built include a resort that can
accommodate up to 1,000 guests and holiday villas nestled in a
virgin forest near Nyingchi.
</P>
<P>
The regional government plans to receive 720,000 Chinese and
foreign visitors in the 2001-2005 period. To reach this target, it
will build an additional 600km of highways, open air routes
between Lhasa and Xigaze and Nyingchi and promote souvenir trade.
</P>
<P>
At present, Tibet has 44 high-grade hotels and 21 travel
agencies. Last year, the region hosted 445,000 visitors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
