<HEADLINE> Earthquake Hits Yunnan Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 27 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.5 on
the Richter scale jolted an area between Qiubei County and Mile
County of southwest China's Yunnan Province at 04:55 (Beijing time)
earlier this morning.
</P>
<P>
According to China Seismological Bureau, the epicenter was
located at 24.2 degrees north latitude and 103.6 degrees east
longitude.
</P>
<P>
Efforts are going on to investigate the casualties and
property losses caused by the quake.
</P>
<P>
Earthquakes measuring 5.9 and 6.5 on the Richter scale hit Yao'
an County of the province on January 15, killing five people and
injuring 1,544. 
</P>
</TEXT>
