<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spain Beats Poland in Euro 2000 Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, January 26 (Xinhua) -- Spain enjoyed a 3-0 victory over
Poland on Wednesday as a warm-up for the European 2000
Championships in the Southeastern port of Cartagena, Spain.
</P>
<P>
Ismael Urzaiz scored two headers and Raul Gonzalez added the
other to help Spain continue its successful streak while Poland
hardly got a look-in throughout the 90 minutes.
</P>
<P>
In the 16th minute, Gonzalez, the 21-year-old Real Madrid
forward, opened the accouting when he exploited a defensive error
by Poland's Ryszard Czerwiec before beating goalkeeper Kadoslaw
Majdan with his left foot.
</P>
<P>
Nine minutes into the second half, Athletic de Bilbao's Urzaiz
headed in from a corner kick and then made it 3-0 four minutes
later with another header from one meter off the line.
</P>
<P>
The match was part of Spain's preparations for the Euro 2000 in
June in the Netherlands and Belgium.
</P>
<P>
Spain, who remained unbeaten in the qualifying group, plans to
stage exhibition games against Croatia, Italy, Sweden and
Luxembourg before the European tournament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
