<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France, Austria Win World Cup Giant Slaloms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, January 26 (Xinhua) -- Matthieu Bozzetto of France
and Ursula Fingerlos of Austria won the men's and women's giant
slalom finals respectively on Wednesday in a FIS World Cup
snowboard competition in Tandadalen, Sweden.
</P>
<P>
Under sunny skies, Bozzetto beat Felix Stadler of Austria for
his season-high third win. Bozzetto, last year's overall champion,
leads compatriot Nicolas Huet 3,940 points to 3,160 in the cup
standings.
</P>
<P>
Defending world champion Richard Richardsson lost to Huet by
four-hundredths of a second in the 16th round and eventually round
up 11th. Huet finished third.
</P>
<P>
Fingerlos beat Isabelle Blanc in the women's giant slalom final.
However, Blanc has a commanding overall lead, 4,600 points to 3,
350 for runner-up Manuela Riegler of Austria.
</P>
<P>
Fingerlos' toughest opponent was Sweden's Sara Fischer, who won
the first semifinal run by .70 seconds. But Fingerlos rallied
strongly in the last part of the second run to edge the Swede.
</P>
<P>
The three-day FIS World Cup snowboard competition resumes on
Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
