<HEADLINE> Ghana LOC to Vote Man-of-the-Match Player in Nations Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, January 26 (Xinhua) -- The Local Organising Committee (
LOC) for the African Nations Cup announced on Wednesday that there
would be a player of the match award from now on in games played
in Ghana.
</P>
<P>
The LOC said the "man-of-the-match" award will be given at
every game played in both Accra and Kumasi, the two centers chosen
for the biennial event here.
</P>
<P>
The award will start from Thursday with the two matches in both
centers. Ghana will meet Togo in Accra while 1996 champions South
Africa will lock horns with unfancied Democratic Republic of Congo
in Kumasi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
