<HEADLINE> Four Egyptian Players Hit by Flu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, January 26 (Xinhua) -- Four Egyptian players, including
striker Yasser Radwan who scored the first goal in his side's 2-0
win over Zambia, are suffering from flu, French coach Gerard Gili
said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Gili said forwards Hazeem Imam and Oumar Mohammed and defender
Hani Ramzy could be sidelined in Egypt's second African Nations
Cup game against Senegal on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Egypt, the defending champions, lead the Nations Cup group C on
goal difference. 
