<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Azerbaijan Might Be Suspended, Blatter Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 26 (Xinhua) -- FIFA president Sepp Blatter
threatened to suspend Azerbaijan's soccer federation (ASF) on
Wednesday if they could not resolve the internal problems.
</P>
<P>
"I have no choice but to call on our emergency committee and I'
m sure that tomorrow it will follow the proposal by the FIFA
president and the ASF will be suspended," Blatter said in a news
conference.
</P>
<P>
Azeri soccer was split into two rival groups. The rebels, led
by the powerful presidents of champions Kepez Ganja and Turan
Tavuz, ignored FIFA's plea for a peaceful solution and went on a
collision course with the ASF.
</P>
<P>
"We must make the governmental authorities listen to the
national associations if they want to remain part of international
football," the FIFA chief said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
