<HEADLINE> Tyson Arrives in Manchester </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 26 (Xinhua) -- American boxer Mike Tyson and
his entourage arrived in Manchester on Wednesday night to a loud
welcome from some 700 fans.
</P>
<P>
The crowd had waited for up to three hours outside the Midland
Hotel in Manchester to get a glimpse of Tyson, who is due to fight
British champion Julius Francis in the city's MEN Arena on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
But Tyson's fans were left disappointed as his handlers bundled
him in through a back door.
</P>
<P>
Tyson, who was convicted of rape in the United States in 1992,
has grabbed the headlines almost every day since flying in to
scenes of hysteria at London's Heathrow Airport on 16 January.
</P>
<P>
He was allowed into Britain after Home Secretary Jack Straw
personally intervened. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000127.0286 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Baggio Sees Future at Inter Milan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 26 (Xinhua) -- Roberto Baggio has vowed to
fight for his Inter Milan future on the day he has been linked
with a loan move to Liverpool.
</P>
<P>
The Italian ace has been out of favour this season with Inter
boss Marcello Lippi but came off the bench on Sunday to score his
first goal of the campaign and Inter's winner in a crucial 2-1
victory at Verona. Now Baggio believes he could be back in Lippi's
plans, following claims he had fallen out with the manager and was
a disruptive influence in the dressing room.
</P>
<P>
The 32-year-old former World Cup star said: "I have never
raised the white flag with Lippi, I'm ready to fight for my place.
If in life you don't fight for things, then there is no chance of
you winning and being able to build something."
</P>
<P>
Baggio rubbished claims of a fall out with his boss and that he
's a troublemaker in the squad, saying: "You saw the way my team-
mates jumped all over me after I scored, and Lippi shook my hand
afterwards. I believe that everything I experienced after that
goal was sincere.
</P>
<P>
"It has been said that I cause trouble in the dressing room,
but now people will have to invent something else. In 18 years in
football I have heard many stupid things, but people should know
the truth.
</P>
<P>
"I accept Lippi's choices, as long as they are honest choices.
It is his job to make decisions."
</P>
<P>
While Baggio is talking about the rebirth of his career at
Inter, there are claims that Liverpool are interested in taking
him on loan as a stop-gap measure to cope with the injuries to
both Michael Owen and Robbie Fowler.
</P>
<P>
Anfield boss Gerard Houllier is known to be scouring Europe in
search of a loan deal, not surprisingly because it is his only
source of top-quality help for his injury-hit squad as under FA
rules Premiership clubs can't sign loan players, except
goalkeepers, from their own league.
</P>
<P>
But with the Champions League and UEFA Cup competitions due to
start again shortly, and work permits required for any player
outside the EU with the transfer deadline only eight weeks away,
Houllier's choices are severely limited.
</P>
<P>
Now it seems that Baggio has eyes for an Inter revival. He
added: "It is not a question of a resurrection in my career, I
never died in the first place." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000127.0287 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Graf to Start Farewell Match Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, January 26 (Xinhua) -- German tennis queen Steffi Graf
will play Czech former world number two Jana Novotna in Stuttgart
on March 3 as the opener of her farewell match tour, according to
the Pascal Room of the Steffi-Graf-Sport Ltd on Wedneyday.
</P>
<P>
The following matches will be held on March 5 and 7 in Berlin
and Oberhausen respectively.
</P>
<P>
As an Image-Ambassadress for Fair-2000 in Hannover, the 31-year-
old Graf will come to the stage to play, but the final date has
yet to be determined.
</P>
<P>
"We shall provide the audience with the wonderful matchs and
Jana Novotna is now in good training," Graf said.
</P>
<P>
The tour will continue in Biscayne and Indian Wells. 
</P>
</TEXT>
