<HEADLINE> Minority Factions to End Boycott in Russian Parliament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Three small factions in the
lower house of the Russian parliament indicated Thursday that they
would end their boycott in the State Duma and return to
parliamentary work on February 9.
</P>
<P>
Deputies of Fatherland-All Russia, the Union of Right Forces
and Yabloko walked out earlier this month during the first session
of the new Duma after the Communist Party and the Unity movement,
the two largest factions, struck a deal on the post of the speaker.
</P>
