Germany's Central Council of Jews, founded in 1950, is an
organization for safeguarding the interests of Jews in Germany.
</P>
<P>
Now there are 80,000 Jews living in Germany, but the relation
between the Jews and Non-Jews is not so good. There are 15 percent
of Germans who take an attitude of antisemitism. 
