<HEADLINE> Cuba Denounces "Inhuman" Treatment to Grandmothers in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, January 27 (Xinhua) -- "Granma," the Cuban Communist
Party daily, Thursday denounced as an "unjust and inhuman
treatment" the meeting held Wednesday by the Cuban boy Elian
Gonzalez and his two grandmothers in Florida.
</P>
<P>
Grandmothers Mariela Quintana and Raquel Rodrguez traveled
Wednesday from Washington to Miami for the meeting with their six-
year-old grandson, who had been retained in Miami for more than
two months.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was scheduled, as agreed upon by the grandmothers
and the U.S. Immigration and Naturalization Service (INS), to be
held at the residence of Sister Jeane O'Laughlin, rector of Barry
University of Miami.
</P>
<P>
As reported by "Granma," Elian Gonzalez entered a site designed
for the meeting accompanied by a nun and a blonde woman, "
something unexpected," because as agreed upon, two nuns should
have taken him to the site of the encounter.
</P>
<P>
The blonde woman is the daughter of Lazaro Gonzalez, a grand-
uncle of the boy,  said "Granma."
</P>
<P>
"Granma" described the woman as "hysterical and very well known
for her diatribes and insults against the true family of Elian,
which reclaims the boy."
</P>
<P>
Mariela ordered then the blonde woman to leave the room.
</P>
<P>
Elian's relatives, including his father, his grandfathers and
great-grandmother, reiterated in a message sent Wednesday to the
grandmothers before their travel to Miami that "under no
circumstances they must agree to meet or have any contact with
Lazaro, his daughter, or any other relative who supported the
child kidnapping."
</P>
<P>
"Granma" said that the grandmothers received "an inhuman
treatment" when security personnel of the residence took a cell
telephone from them through which the grandmothers and the boy had
talked with the relatives in Cuba.
</P>
<P>
The grandmothers said that Elian left them a gratifying and
affectionate impression, although "the famous residence was for
them a prison and an isolation."
</P>
<P>
Elian was found clinging to an inner tube off the Florida
coast on Nov. 25. He had left Cuba with his mother, who died along
with her boyfriend and nine others when their boat capsized.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
