<HEADLINE> Nine Die in Combats in Colombia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Fighting between the
Colombian army and rebels of the Revolutionary Armed Forces of
Colombia (FARC) Thursday left nine dead and six injured in the
municipality of Lejanias, said the authorities.
</P>
<P>
The combats occurred in a mountainous terrain close to the zone
of dissension, where the government and the FARC maintain a peace
dialogue.
</P>
<P>
Seventh Army Brigade commander General Francisco Pedraza said
that the dead were seven rebels and two soldiers, and the injured
six army troops.
</P>
<P>
The injured soldiers were taken to a sanitary post in
Villavicencio, 230 kilometers southeast of Santafe de Bogota.
</P>
</TEXT>
